  "prompt": "What are some ways to put underline and Bold text in Facebook Chat? As previously we can do this by putting text in between underscore(_) and asterisk(*) for underline and bold text respectively?",
  "response": "As of October 2023, Facebook Chat (including Facebook Messenger) offers limited text formatting options directly within the platform. While some basic formatting like **bold** and *italics* can be achieved using specific symbols, **underlining text** isn't natively supported through simple markdown-like syntax. However, there are several methods you can use to format your text in Facebook Chat:\n\n### 1. **Using Asterisks and Underscores for Bold and Italics**\n\n- **Bold Text:** Enclose your text within asterisks (`*`) to make it bold.\n  \n  **Example:**\n  ```\n  *This text will be bold*\n  ```\n  **Result:** *This text will be bold*\n\n- **Italics:** Enclose your text within underscores (`_`) to italicize it.\n  \n  **Example:**\n  ```\n  _This text will be italicized_\n  ```\n  **Result:** _This text will be italicized_\n\n### 2. **Creating Underlined Text**\n\nFacebook Chat doesn't support underlining text through simple markdown syntax (like using underscores or other symbols). However, you can achieve underlined text by using **Unicode characters** that mimic underlined styles. Here's how:\n\n- **Using Online Text Generators:**\n  \n  - **Step 1:** Visit a Unicode text generator website such as [LingoJam](https://lingojam.com/UnderlineTextGenerator) or [YayText](https://yaytext.com/underline-text/).\n  \n  - **Step 2:** Enter the text you want to underline in the provided input box.\n  \n  - **Step 3:** The generator will display your text in various styles, including underlined versions.\n  \n  - **Step 4:** Copy the underlined text and paste it into your Facebook Chat.\n\n  **Example:**\n  ```\n  \u0332T\u0332h\u0332i\u0332s\u0332 \u0332t\u0332e\u0332x\u0332t\u0332 \u0332i\u0332s\u0332 \u0332u\u0332n\u0332d\u0332e\u0332r\u0332l\u0332i\u0332n\u0332e\u0332d\u0332\n  ```\n\n### 3. **Combining Bold and Underline**\n\nIf you wish to have both bold and underlined text, you can combine the methods above:\n\n- **Step 1:** Use a Unicode generator that supports both bold and underline.\n- **Step 2:** Generate the combined style and copy-paste it into your chat.\n\n**Example:**\n```\n\ud835\udc13\ud835\udc21\ud835\udc22\ud835\udc2c \ud835\udc22\ud835\udc2c \ud835\udc01\ud835\udc28\ud835\udc25\ud835\udc1d \ud835\udc1a\ud835\udc27\ud835\udc1d \ud835\udc14\ud835\udc27\ud835\udc1d\ud835\udc1e\ud835\udc2b\ud835\udc25\ud835\udc22\ud835\udc27\ud835\udc1e\ud835\udc1d\n```\n\n*Note:* Not all devices or platforms may render these Unicode styles correctly, and excessive use might affect readability.\n\n### 4. **Using Messenger's Built-in Features (Limited)**\n\nWhile Facebook Messenger doesn't offer extensive text formatting options, it does support sending **stickers, emojis, and GIFs** which can help emphasize your messages. Additionally, you can use **text effects** when sending messages in some cases:\n\n- **Text Effects:**\n  \n  - **Step 1:** Open the Messenger app and tap on the text field.\n  \n  - **Step 2:** Type your message.\n  \n  - **Step 3:** Press and hold the send button (usually an arrow) to see available text effects like \"Bold,\" \"Italic,\" \"Slide,\" \"Echo,\" etc.\n  \n  - **Step 4:** Choose the desired effect and send your message.\n\n*Note:* The availability of text effects may vary based on updates and platform (iOS, Android, Web).\n\n### 5. **Third-Party Keyboard Apps**\n\nSome third-party keyboard apps offer additional text formatting options, including bold, italics, and underlined text. By installing such keyboards, you can access a variety of styles directly from your keyboard while typing in Facebook Chat.\n\n**Popular Options:**\n- **Unicode Text Keyboard**\n- **FancyKey**\n- **Cool Fonts for Instagram, WhatsApp, etc.**\n\n*Ensure you download reputable apps to protect your privacy and device security.*\n\n### **Conclusion**\n\nWhile Facebook Chat doesn't natively support extensive text formatting like underlining through simple symbols, you can still achieve bold and italic styles using asterisks and underscores. For underlining and more advanced formatting, leveraging Unicode text generators or third-party tools is the most effective approach. Always be cautious when using third-party services to ensure your data and privacy remain secure.",
